1. install arch as you would normally
	-Don't forget to install base-devel along with base (with pacstrap)
2. make user "sam" and give him root priveliges
3. install yay
4. install openssh package
5. install yadm-git (not 'yadm')
6. copy id_rsa over to new computer (you can use scp or just email or whatever I guess)
7. clone the yadm repo (with yadm, not git!)
8. cat .packs-to-install | yay -S -
9. sudo systemctl enable NetworkManager
10. scp the contents of ~/.gnupg
11. git clone blah@blah ~/.password-store
12. maybe install tlp if it's a laptop (and don't forget to enable the service)
13. maybe install nvidia package
